Can you name some famous scientists who have made significant contributions to our understanding of genetics and DNA?
Some notable geneticists include James Watson, Francis Crick, Rosalind Franklin, and Barbara McClintock. Each of these scientists played a pivotal role in uncovering the structure of DNA, its replication process, or the genetic factors that influence biological traits and hereditary diseases. Their groundbreaking discoveries have led to advancements in molecular biology and genetics, significantly impacting our understanding of life at the cellular level.
